NETWORK-001-v1.0 Stabilization as network resilience problem Measured viability via connection redundancy 9/8/9/8 8.5
ADAPTIVE-001-v1.0 Apply agile sprint methodology to socio-technical systems Proposed iterative, test-based approach 8/9/7/7 7.75
FMEA-001-v1.0 ⭐ Failure as predictable domino effect via FMEA Provided concrete, testable risk framework 10/7/10/8 8.75
INSTITUTIONAL-001-v1.0 Create simulated Martian Resource Credit market Addressed economic signaling in closed system 8/8/6/7 7.25
EXO-ECONOMIC-001-v1.0 Positive feedback between economy and planetary cycles Linked economic activity to biosphere metrics 7/10/5/8 7.5

Selection Rationale: FMEA-001 offered superior testability and coherence, transforming abstract "gaps" into specific, analyzable failure sequences that could inform engineering and social design.

